message: There's a better one far East, and I think the original is west someplace in the mountains but I'm not too sure
They were great but the dungeons should have been more fleshed out as opposed to simply being what I consider a triple/quad shrine.
I find guardian gear doesn't have the best durability.  Your best bet  would be the coliseum north of the Plateau or hyrule castle
At least you got the big ones, those are fun to fight. The small ones are annoying

It'll have however many hearts are currently saved onto the amiibo at the time you use it. If you use it now it'll have 3 of course and if you do the cave of Shadows it will have however many you save onto it
It's not always an npc sometimes it's a stone slate or a book

Yes you do. It's easy if you know the layout. I'd say pretty hard if you dont
I just take funny ones for things like the master sword and Hyland shield

Upper levels. Quite a bit laying around, you'll find it without even trying.

In raw defense, yeah. But you won't get any set bonuses or any armor type bonuses.
